# README #

This readme will document whatever steps are necessary to get the web automation running.

### What is this repository for ###

This code covers the exercise 2 related to the automation of a front end.

HiberusMavenProject/

* GoogleAutoSearch.java         # Automatiza la búsqueda de "Automatización" en Google, selecciona el link de Wikipedia, comprueba el año en que se hizo el 1er proceso automático y toma una captura de pantalla
* Readme.txt  # Archivo con instrucciones para ejecución en IntelliJ IDEA


### Download and installation ###

* Download the corresponding git repository from: https://github.com/angvazcar/HiberusMaven
* Execute the following comands on your prompt/terminal:
_git clone https://github.com/angvazcar/HiberusMaven.git_

### Preconditions before code execution ###

*  Have Java version 11 or higher installed (you can download from here (https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#java11?er=221886)
*  Have IntelliJ IDEA installed
*  Have Maven installed
*  Have Selenium WebDriver installed
*  Have ChromeDriver installed and configured
*  Add dependencies in IntelliJ

### Usage and code execution ###

* Open the project downloaded in the previous steps with IntelliJ (File--> Open and select the downloaded folder)
* In IntelliJ terminal add the dependencies manually (File-->Project Structure-->Dependencies click on + and add the jar files from JAR files dependencies folder
* Open GoogleAutoSearch.java from src folder in IntelliJ
* Change the chromedriver path from the one on your computer (replace "/Users/angelesbuild38/Documents/Chromedriver/chromedriver" with your driver path usually in Windows:"c:\path\to\your\chromedriver.exe" and Mac: "usr/local/bin/chromedriver" 
* Save the changes
* Click on the run green button on the left of the code line _public static void main(String[] args)_ (if you do not see it in the top right corner,right click on GoogleAutoSearch.java and select Run 'GoogleAutoSearch.main()')


Once the execution has finshed you should get
* a screenshot named: wiki_screenshot.png on your repo path
* printed the year of the first automation process
